t focuses on the school program launched in Palermo during the mid-1990s, which was designed to break the Mafia’s territorial and mental control.Combining theories on social capital and civic education, the author presents and analyses new quantitative and qualitative research carried out in seven public schools in Palermo. This book will be valuable to students, academics and researchers interested in social capital and trust, Italian politics, civic education, organised crime, local government and democratic practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivil societyzItalyzPalermo. 0aCooperationzItalyzPalermo. 0aEducationxSocial aspectszItalyzPalermo. 0aMafiazItalyzPalermo. 0aSocial capital (Sociology)zItalyzPalermo. 0aTrust. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh  aMafia.  aPalermo.  acivic education.  ademocracy.  adistrust.  aeconomic development.  ageneralised trust.  anon-cooperation.  apublic action.  asocial capital.1 aBäck, Hanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGunnarson, Carina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInkinen, Magdalena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779217440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847792174423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847792174/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles